<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">NOTICE OF MOTION</TI>
<P>The Defendants, Watch Tower Bible and Tract Society of Pennsylvania (&ldquo;WTPA&rdquo;) and Watchtower Bible and Tract Society of New York, Inc. (&ldquo;WTNY&rdquo;), will make a motion (&ldquo;Motion&rdquo;) before The Honourable Justice Perell on May 2, 2019 at 10:00 a.m., or as soon after that time as the motion can he heard, at the court house, 393 University Avenue, Toronto, Ontario.</P>
<P><BOLD>PROPOSED METHOD OF HEARING:</BOLD> The Motion is to be heard orally.</P>
<P><BOLD>THE MOTION IS FOR:</BOLD></P>
<P>1. An Order:
<P1>(a) Striking the Tuovi Affidavits (as defined below) in their entirety; or</P1>
<P1>(b) In the alternative, striking the Improper Tuovi Content (as defined below); and</P1></P>
<P>2. The costs of the Motion; and</P>
<P>3. Such further and other relief as this Court may deem just, all without submission or attornment by WYNY or WTPA (the &ldquo;U.S. Defendants&rdquo;) to the jurisdiction of this Court.</P>
<P><BOLD>THE GROUNDS FOR THE MOTION ARE:</BOLD></P>
<P>1. This Motion relates to the evidence delivered in respect of the motion of the U.S. Defendants challenging the jurisdiction of this Court in relation to the claims asserted against them. For greater certainty, the U.S. Defendants do not submit or attorn to the jurisdiction of this Court.</P>
<P>2. The plaintiff has delivered affidavits of Peter Tuovi sworn on August 3, 2018, January 2, 2019, and April 2, 2019 (collectively, the &ldquo;Tuovi Affidavits&rdquo;). Leave of this Court is required, but has not been obtained, to serve and file the Tuovi Affidavit sworn April 2, 2019.</P>
<P>3. Peter Tuovi is a partner in the law firm McPhadden Samac Tuovi, which is the firm of lawyers acting for the plaintiff in these proceedings.</P>
<P>4. The contents of the Tuovi Affidavits constitute the evidence of Bryan McPhadden, as each of the Touvi Affidavits states that &ldquo;[e]xcept where otherwise specifically indicated below, I am advised of the following by Mr. McPhadden and verily believe same to be true&rdquo;.</P>
<P>5. Bryan McPhadden is also a partner in the law firm McPhadden Samac Tuovi. Mr. McPhadden has carriage of this action on behalf of the plaintiff, and he is the sole listed counsel on the motions presently before the Court that are returnable August 2, 2019 (&ldquo;August Motions&rdquo;).</P>
<P>6. The Tuovi Affidavits ought to be struck in their entirety because they are improper solicitors' affidavits and, further, it is improper for Bryan McPhadden to appear as counsel on his own affidavits. In the alternative, Mr. McPhadden is precluded from appearing at the oral hearing of the August Motions.</P>
<P>7. The Tuovi Affidavits are not limited to perceived facts but are replete with improper speculation, argument, conclusions, and opinions. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the following paragraphs of the Tuovi Affidavits are improper on this basis:
<P1>(a) Touvi Affidavit sworn August 3, 2018: Paragraphs 8-9, 12&ndash;14, 18&ndash;20, 22, 24, 29&ndash;33, 35, and 41;</P1>
<P1>(b) Tuovi Affidavit sworn January 2, 2019: Paragraphs 4, 6, 12-13, 16-17, 20&ndash;25, 28, 30&ndash;33, 35, 37&ndash;39, 41, 44&ndash;48, 52-53, 56&ndash;58, 62&ndash;64, 66-67, 69, 71, 73-74, 76&ndash;79, 81, 87&ndash;102, 104&ndash;107, 109-110, and 113; and</P1>
<P1>(c) Tuovi Affidavit sworn April 2, 2019: Paragraphs 9&ndash;14.</P1></P>
<P>8. The Tuovi Affidavit sworn January 2, 2019 improperly asserts contested facts on the information and believe from the plaintiff and proposed plaintiffs. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, paragraphs 7, 8, 10, 11, and 15 of the Tuovi Affidavit sworn January 2, 2019 are improper on that basis.</P>
<P>9. Leaving the Tuovi Affidavits on the record would be embarrassing and prejudicial to the fair hearing of the August Motions.</P>
<P>10. The substantial defects in the Tuovi Affidavits are such that they should be struck in their entirety pursuant to Rule 25.11 of the <EM>Rules of Civil Procedure</EM>, R.R.O. 1990, Reg. 194. The substantial defects in the Tuovi Affidavits are intertwined with all other parts of the Tuovi Affidavits, making the entire documents defective.</P>
<P>11. In the alternative, if the Tuovi Affidavits are not struck out in their entirety, the paragraphs of the Tuovi Affidavits referred to within this Notice of Motion, together with all exhibits attached thereto (collectively, the &ldquo;Improper Tuovi Content&rdquo;), should be struck pursuant to Rule 25.11.</P>
<P>12. Rules 1.04, 4.06(2), 25.11, 37, 39, 57 of the <EM>Rules of Civil Procedure</EM>.</P>
<P>13. Such further and other grounds as the lawyers may advise.</P>
<P><BOLD>THE FOLLOWING DOCUMENTARY EVIDENCE</BOLD> will be used at the hearing of the Motion:
<P1>(a) The Tuovi Affidavits;</P1>
<P1>(b) The pleadings and proceedings herein;</P1>
<P1>(c) Such further and other evidence as the lawyers may advise and this Court may permit.</P1></P>
