<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">AFFIDAVIT OF PETER E. TUOVI (Sworn August 3, 2018)</TI>
<P>I, PETER E. TUOVI, of the City of Toronto, in the Province of Ontario, MAKE OATH AND SAY AS FOLLOWS:
<P1>1. I am a lawyer in the law firm McPhadden Samac Tuovi, lawyers for the plaintiff herein and, as such, have knowledge of the matters to which I hereinafter depose. The lawyer at our firm with carriage of this action is Bryan C. McPhadden. Except where otherwise specifically indicated below, I am advised of the following Bryan C. McPhadden and verily believe same to be true.</P1>
<P1>2. The herein action is a proposed sex abuse action against a religious organization known as the Jehovah's Witnesses (&ldquo;JW Organization&rdquo;).</P1>
<P1>3. Generally speaking, the primary allegation in the action is that the JW Organization failed to maintain adequate policies and procedures to prevent and address sexual abuse within the organization.</P1>
<P1>4. Amongst the asserted deficiencies in the policies and procedures is that they put the interests of the JW Organization ahead of sex abuse victims.</P1>
<P1>5. The alleged deficiencies include inadequate and ineffective policies and procedures for preventing sex abuse and reporting alleged sex abuse to public authorities.</P1>
<P1>6. Another assertion is that die organization does not accept the veracity of alleged victim's sex abuse allegations unless there were two witnesses to the abuse (the &ldquo;Two Witness Rule&rdquo;).</P1>
<P1>7. The herein action was commenced by way of Statement of Claim issued September 26, 2017 a copy of which is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD>. A copy of the draft Amended claim is attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;R&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P1>
<P1>8. In preparing to commence this action, it was not an easy task to identify the JW Organization corporations to name as it was necessary to sort through the labyrinth of Jehovah's Witness corporations. The specific roles of individual JW Organization corporations are rarely found or, if found, stated. On the organization's website some specific corporations are identified though only brief and generalized descriptions of their roles are provided. By way of example, attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> to my affidavit is the organization's webpage for the defendant Watch Tower Bible and Tract Society of Pennsylvania. There, the organization notes:
<QUOTE><P>Besides the Watch Tower Bible and Tract Society of Pennsylvania (&ldquo;JWPA&rdquo;), Jehovah's Witnesses use dozens of legal entities in various countries.</P></QUOTE></P1>
<P1>9. Relative to the overall control and administration of the JW Organization, the aforementioned webpage advises, in respect of JWPA, that:
<QUOTE><P>The corporation members and directors assist the Governing Body of Jehovah's Witnesses (the &ldquo;Governing Body&rdquo;).</P></QUOTE></P1>
<P1>10. As regards the Governing Body, JW Organization's website says:
<QUOTE><P>The Governing Body is a small group of mature Christians who provide direction for Jehovah's Witnesses worldwide.</P></QUOTE></P1>
<P1>11. The website further indicates that the Governing Body is composed of 8 men who serve at the JW Organization's world headquarters in Warwick, New York, United States. Attached to my affidavit and marked <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> is a Copy of the webpage about the Governing Body.</P1>
<P1>12. The webpage relating to JWPA notes that the JW Organization use JWPA to support their worldwide work, which includes publishing Bibles and Bible-based literature. While JWPA's activities may be &ldquo;worldwide&rdquo;, there are JW Organization entities in many countries including Canada. The JW Organization's corporation in Canada is the defendant Watch Tower Bible and Tract Society of Canada (&ldquo;JWCan&rdquo;).</P1>
<P1>13. The JW Organization's aforementioned website describes, in a very general way, the objectives of JWPA:
<QUOTE><P>According to its charter, the corporation's purposes are &ldquo;religious, educational, and charitable,&rdquo; in particular, to &ldquo;preach and teach the gospel of God's Kingdom under Christ Jesus.&rdquo;</P></QUOTE></P1>
<P1>14. The fact of the matter is that it is impossible for an outsider to determine the exact responsibilities of the &ldquo;dozens&rdquo; of JW corporations. Conversely, it is impossible to determine which JW corporation is responsible for developing and enforcing the JW Organization's sex abuse policies and procedures.</P1>
<P1>15. A search of &ldquo;sex abuse&rdquo; on the JW organization's website does not disclose a responsible organization.</P1>
<P1>16. A search on the same website of the &ldquo;Watchtower Bible and Tract Society of New York&rdquo; (&ldquo;JWNY&rdquo;) (another defendant herein) does not result in a description of that corporation or its responsibilities and the search simply return to the above noted JWPA page.</P1>
<P1>17. JWPA was incorporated in New York State 1884. In 2001, it filed Articles of Amendment, a copy of which is attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD>. The Articles identify the corporation's objectives.</P1>
<P1>18. Also attached to my affidavit aid marked <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;E&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the Charter for JWNY, updated to September, 2003. The purposes of JWNY stated therein are the same as for JWPA.</P1>
<P1>19. From the incorporating documents of JWPA and JWNY it is not possible to discern roles and responsibilities of the corporations within the JW Organization as directed by the Governing Body.</P1>
<P1>20. From our research, it appears that both JWPA and JWNY have some role in the development and implementation of the JW Organizations' sex abuse policies and procedures.</P1>
<P1>21. The JW Organization distributes its publication &ldquo;Awake!&rdquo;. On its website can be found articles appearing in previous editions. An example of such an article relating to sex abuse is titled &ldquo;If Your Child is Abused&rdquo;. A copy of that article is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;F&rdquo;</BOLD>. The header above the article suggests the article appeared in a 1993 edition of Awake!. From a notation at the end of the article it can be noted that JWP asserts a copyright relative to the article.</P1>
<P1>22. Based on the foregoing, our understanding was that the sex abuse policies of the JW Organization were previously established on a worldwide basis by either the defendant Watch Tower Bible and Tract Society of Pennsylvania and/or the Watch Tower Bible and Tract Society of New York, Inc.</P1>
<P1>23. When this action was commenced, we were unaware of the existence or role of a corporation by the name of the Christian Congregation of Jehovah's Witnesses (&ldquo;CCJW&rdquo;). CCJW was incorporated in New York State on August 15, 2000. Attached to my affidavit and marked <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;G&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the Certificate of Incorporation.</P1>
<P1>24. As may be noted from Article III in the Certificate of Incorporation, the proposed defendant CCJW has entirely the same stated purposes as do the existing defendants JWPA and JWNY.</P1>
<P1>25. A brief description of CCJW is found online at: <UNDER>https://wwwfacebook.com/pg/christiancongregation/about/?ref=page_Internal</UNDER> A copy of the page at that link is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;H&rdquo;</BOLD>. There, it stated:
<QUOTE><P>The Christian Congregation of Jehovah's Witnesses is a non-profit organization operating in various countries worldwide.</P></QUOTE></P1>
<P1>The countries in which CCJW operates or whether it operates in Canada are not indicated there.</P1>
<P1>26. One of the CCJW letters posted on line is dated October 1, 2012, a copy of which is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;I&rdquo;</BOLD>. It is addressed to All Bodies of Elders and is in reference to &ldquo;Child Abuse&rdquo;. The table of contents at the beginning of the letters discloses that &ldquo;child sexual abuse&rdquo; is one of the matters addressed therein. The first line of the letter says it updates 9 earlier letters to all bodies of elders regarding child abuse. Four of those letters pre-date incorporation of CCJW.</P1>
<P1>27. One of the 4 letters predating the incorporation of CCJW is said to be dated February 3, 1993. Found online is a letter bearing the same date said to be issued by JWNY and is in reference to &ldquo;victims of child abuse&rdquo; and includes discussion about &ldquo;sexual abuse.&rdquo; A copy of the said letter is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;J&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P1>
<P1>28. Another of the letters predating CCJW's incorporation is said to be dated March 14, 1997. Found online is a JWNY letter bearing the same date, addressed To All Bodies of Elders and, as appears from the second paragraph of the letter, is about &lsquo;child sexual abuse&rsquo;. Attached to my affidavit and marked <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;K&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the said letter dated March 14, 1997.</P1>
<P1>29. Also found online is a virtually identical letter of the same but issued by the &ldquo;Bible and Tract Society of Britain&rdquo;. Attached to my affidavit and marked <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;L&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the said letter. The fact that a Jehovah's Witness organization in Britain is sending the same letter as that sent by JWNY suggests that JWNY prescribes what the British organization is to distribute to its Elders.</P1>
<P1>30. As, in its October 1, 2012 letter, CCJW is updating 4 letters previously issued by JWNY regarding child abuse, including those sent by JWNY, it now appears that CCJW has assumed at least some, and perhaps all, the JWNY's responsibilities for instructing Elders on the issue of sex abuse. In this regard it is also noteworthy that following the date of CCJW's first letter on sex abuse, no letters issued by JWNY on this issue of sex abuse can be located.</P1>
<P1>31. It now appears that in the early 2000's responsibility for such policies was transferred by the JW Organization to CCJW. Accordingly, to the extent there are deficiencies and defects in the sex abuse policies of the JW Organization, they are the responsibility of CCJW.</P1>
<P1>32. At the time this action was commenced we were not aware of the existence of CCJW and, therefore, not aware of the role it played or may have played as regards the JW Organizations sex abuse policies and procedures.</P1>
<P1>33. It appears that CCJW may also direct the affairs JWCan and other JW Organizations in other jurisdictions in respect of sexual abuse policies. I refer in this regard to three more letters found online. The three were issued by JWCan and the JW Organizations in Britain and Australia. They are dated October 1, 2012 the same date as the above noted CCJW letter. The three other letters are virtually identical to the said CCJW letter. The copies of the October 1, 2012 JWCan and the British and Australian letters are attached hereto and respectively marked <BOLD>Exhibits &ldquo;M&rdquo;, &ldquo;N&rdquo;, and &ldquo;O&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P1>
<P1>34. Given that JWCan bears a strikingly similar name to those of JWPA and JWNY, it struck us that a corporation with a name similar to that of CCJW may also have been incorporated in Canada. Our searches disclosed no such entity. Attached to may affidavit and marked <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;P&rdquo;</BOLD> are the results of a Federal corporate name search. There is no corporation with a name similar to CCJW. We also conducted a corporate name search in Ontario, a copy of which is attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;Q&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P1>
<P1>35. On learning that the existing defendants may have little or nothing to do with the JW Organization's sex abuse policies and procedures since the early 2000's and about the time CCJW was incorporated, we reviewed our data bank of individuals who have contacted us about this case and identified possible representative plaintiffs to act in respect of those claims and, in particular, as regards the potential liability of CCJW. The said process identified as Melissa White. Based on information provided to us by Her, we have prepared the draft Amended Statement of Claim which sets out her allegations, including those relating to CCJW. Melissa White has indicated to us her interest in and desire to be added as a representative plaintiff in this action.</P1>
<P1>36. Our firm has now been retained by the two proposed representative plaintiffs to pursue claims on behalf of class members on whose behalf they might act.</P1>
<P1>37. Our firm has also had contact with another alleged sex abuse victim, by the name of Sandra Hall. All her circumstances relate to Ontario, where she presently resides The draft Amended Statement of Claim also contains allegations relating to her experiences.</P1>
<P1>38. I note that a plurality of the many dozens of alleged Jehovah's Witness sex abuse victims who have contacted our firm state that they did or now reside in Ontario and/or were sexually abused in Ontario.</P1>
<P1>39. The plaintiff, Christian Gutierrez, consents to the Melissa White and Sandra Hall being added as plaintiffs and proposed representative plaintiffs in this action.</P1>
<P1>40. Melissa White and Sandra Hall consent to being added as plaintiffs and proposed representative plaintiffs.</P1>
<P1>41. Based on the foregoing, I believe CCJW is a proper and necessary defendant to this proceeding Mid that Sandra Hall and Melissa White are proper and necessary plaintiffs.</P1>
<P1>42. Also based on the foregoing, we propose that the Statement of Claim be amended in accordance with the draft Amended Statement of Claim attached hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;R&rdquo;</BOLD> and that the title of proceedings be amended to accord with that identified in the Notice of Motion.</P1></P>
<P>I swear this affidavit to give my evidence herein and for no other or improper purpose.</P>
